==English==

===Noun===
'''chuff'''

#A coarse or stupid fellow.

===Intransitive verb===
'''to chuff'''
# To make [[noisy]] [[puffing]] [[sound]]s, as of a [[steam]] [[locomotive]]

===Slang Terms===
#(slang: coarse) The anus.
#(British) Surly.  Also "chuffy."
#(slang: coarse) Swolen (cheeks).  Also "chuffy."
#(slang: writing/show business) In writing, especially scriptwriting, superfluous small talk that: 
##is free of conflict.
##offers no character development, description or insight.
##does not advance the story or plot.
:'''For example:'''  
::HE: Hi.  
::SHE: Hi.  
::HE: How you doing?  
::SHE: Okay.  How are you?  
::HE: Okay.  Nice weather we're having.  
::SHE: Yeah.

